Alfa reports **four mutually exclusive W3C ACT outcomes**:

| Outcome       | Meaning                                                                 | Action                                                                 |
|---------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `Passed`      | Rule definitively passes ‚Äî no further action needed                    | Log for conformance report; no fix needed                             |
| `Failed`      | Rule definitively fails ‚Äî violation confirmed                          | Fix in code; verify with `Audit.run()` again                          |
| `Inapplicable`| Rule does not apply to this page (e.g., no images, no links)          | No action needed; document context why rule wasn‚Äôt applicable         |
| `Can't Tell`  | Insufficient evidence to determine pass/fail ‚Äî requires manual review  | Manually inspect with screen reader/keyboard; document justification  |

