The `Playwright.toPage()` wrapper ensures Alfa can reliably introspect the live DOM and compute accessibility state using the same viewport and focus context as Playwright.

Alfa‚Äôs `Audit.run()` returns `Iterable<RuleOutcome>`. Each `RuleOutcome` has an `outcome` property whose value is one of: `Passed`, `Failed`, `Can't Tell`, or `Inapplicable`.

**Example: Filter and report only actionable issues**
```ts
import { Playwright } from '@siteimprove/alfa-playwright';
import { Audit } from '@siteimprove/alfa-act-rules';

const alfaPage = Playwright.toPage(page);
const results = await Audit.run(alfaPage, ['WCAG2AA']);

const issues = [...results].filter(
  (r) => r.outcome === 'Failed' || r.outcome === "Can't Tell"
);

if (issues.length === 0) {
  console.log('No accessibility issues found (or all require manual review).');
} else {
  console.log(`Found ${issues.length} issues requiring attention:`);
  issues.forEach((r, i) => {
    console.log(`${i + 1}. ${r.rule.identifier} ‚Üí ${r.outcome}`);
    console.log(`   Description: ${r.description}`);
  });
}
```

**Why treat "Can't Tell" as manual review?**
- Alfa‚Äôs static analysis cannot determine intent (e.g., missing alt text *could* be decorative or *could* be an error)
- Example: `<img src="chart.png">` ‚Üí Alfa returns `Can't Tell` for `H30` (alt text required)
- A human must inspect the context to decide: add alt text, or mark as decorative with `alt=""`
- Therefore, "Can't Tell" items belong in a **manual review queue**, not auto-passed.

**Pro tip:** Exclude `Inapplicable` and `Passed` in QA reports to reduce noise.

**Architecture comparison**:

| Feature | axe-core | @siteimprove/alfa-playwright |
|--------|----------|------------------------------|
| **Core model** | Rule engine on DOM snapshot | Rule engine on Alfa‚Äôs own document model |
| **Evaluation** | Runs in browser context (`axe.run()`) | Runs via `Audit.run(alfaPage)` after `Playwright.toPage()` |
| **Result shape** | `axe.Result[]` with `violations`, `passes`, `incomplete` | `Result[]` with explicit `outcome: Passed | Failed | Can't Tell | Inapplicable` |
| **ACT conformance** | Partial (some rules only map loosely) | Full W3C ACT outcomes by design |
| **Type safety** | JavaScript-first, no strict TS types | Fully typed in TypeScript |
| **Rule granularity** | Coarser, some rules aggregate multiple checks | Fine-grained, one check per result |

**Migration pattern**:
```ts
