Yes ‚Äî you can run both engines *sequentially* on the same page snapshot, but **not in parallel** due to DOM mutation side effects. Cross-validation is valid, but outcomes are not directly comparable because:

| Engine       | W3C ACT Outcome Mapping | Rule Coverage      |
|--------------|------------------------|--------------------|
| axe-core     | `violations`, `passes`, `incomplete`, `inapplicable` | Proprietary subset (mostly AA) |
| @siteimprove/alfa-playwright | `Passed` / `Failed` / `Inapplicable` / `Can't Tell` | WCAG 2.2 AA spec-compliant ACT rules |

